caption: Service is great. The manager is a great guy. Their protein choices are top of the line with grass fed meats.

Delicious and plenty of options to make your own. Great for a healthy alternative and very filling. Love the couscous and pickled onions as well as the kale and corn additions. Friendly staff welcomed me and had a nice, quick chat. Made me wish I was a local.
Super fresh ingredients. Lots of veggies, big portions, good prices, excellent service!

Our family eats A LOT of Mediterranean food & my daughter and I agreed that this is some of the best. She had a chicken pita and I had a salad with falafel. Both so delicious but the falafel was especially fantastic.
I LOVE this location great food and friendly people
The protein portion is getting smaller each time I go.
A reasonable fast food alternative
Amazing food, good customer service, online ordering is easy - top notch Mediterranean
I love this place, the fresh food, the new menu - but mostly the amazing staff. They go above and beyond in every way. My favorite place to lunch in the West Loop. Thank you so much!!

I’ll be honest I ate at this location 2-3 times a week for a few months when it first opened.  One fateful day there was a RUBBER BAND in my food, luckily saw it before I swallowed/ate it.  Needless to say it was the last day I will ever eat at any Roti.  Naf Naf come to find out is significantly better anyways. I typically don’t ever leave one star reviews, and try to give the benefit of the doubt when I can - but a rubber band in a plate of food is simply not ok.
The employees are EXCELLENT!  Food is inexpensive, healthy choices and portion sizes are huge!!
Good food. They have nutrition information on the menu. Good price.
Food was good. Friendly staff.

I don't usually write reviews but I have to write a review for this place. I was having lunch with my friends here and literally just after the last bite of my meal the manager tolled us that we should leave and that we are not welcome to stay after finishing lunch!! He literally came to our table and took our dishes away!! How rude and disrespectful!!
So good! The signature plate is that deal!
Tasty.
Amazing!!

Honestly, we weren't expecting too much when we saw this restaurant pop up on google maps, and when walking into the place nothing changed our mind. THEN...we actually ate. WOW! Simply put, the food is GREAT! Good sized portions and the flavors were very, very good. I highly recommend this place for anyone, but especially if you're looking for vegetarian/vegan, this is a great place to try.
Ordered Lamb meat balls - very salty - it's bad Chicken - it's like chewing an elastic substance with little to no flavor.. Sides are good...
Rick!!! Ask for Rick next time you are at this Roti location - the nicest and most genuine man! Best spot for lunch in the Loop! 🙌🏼
Not Mediterranean, more Greek and Pakistani combined. Low quality food and the falafel is terrible

Always fresh, friendly and fast...Roti on Randolph is my go-to lunch spot.  I frequent this location multiple times per week due to the value (especially with the rewards app) and quantity of healthy options.  Rick, the manager, makes a conscious effort to get to know his customers on a personal level rarely found in a quick serve environment.  The staff is always energized and cleanliness is always prioritized.  Keep up the great work and great product.  I look forward to many more future visits.
I love this place! Delicious, fresh food and great service.

I love Roti!  The food is always warm and you leave full.. The manager makes you feel welcomed and is always pleasant to talk too. The restaurant is very clean and it's always a pleasure when I go in for lunch!

This place is fantastic. I love the wide variety of sides to spice up your Mediterranean lunch/dinner. I think the red sug sauce is very unique and my go to when visiting their loop location. Great customer service with fantastically friendly workers. Hands down my fav lunch spot.
Great selection. Healthier choice. Great tasting food

If you enjoy a restaurant with Mediterranean food and an extremely polite staff then this specific Roti location is all you will ever need!  I go here at least 2-3 times a week, and the service along with the food only keeps getting better!

Roti has always been my go to restaurants whenever I want to have a quick Lunch or Dinner. Be it the salads or the rice plates Mediterranean food never gets boring and is never too heavy on your tummy. More than the food, the staff has always been courteous and welcoming and there’s never been a bad day for me at Roti (200 W Randolph St). I absolutely love the place and the reward program on the Roti App ensures you get your pay back for every $50 spent. Roti is definitely a must visit restaurant for anyone who wants to try something quick that’s neither too heavy on your tummy nor too heavy on your pocket
Okayish. Too bland for my taste. The flavor profile is generic at best.

Some of the best fast food mediterranean in Chicago.  Everything is so fresh, organic, and overall good.  I'm partial to the chicken roti, but the falafel is some of the best I have ever had.  It just falls apart when you eat it and it's so rich in flavor you aren't even tempted to dip it in a sauce.
Best felafel in Chicago from a chain.
Great Staff. Better Food.
Decent fast Mediterranean,  clean.  I got the salad with chicken and it was not dry:)
Good as always
It’s was a busy lunch hour but the service was still fast and friendly. The food was amazing!
Amazing staff.... Very fresh wonderful food
Not impressed with the portions for the price.

This place is incredible. Well managed, great food, great team. I forgot my wallet today and was going to leave to go grab some cash from the ATM (using my phone) but the manager stopped me and told me to eat first. He said Roti is better hot than it is cold. That kind of service is too rare in today’s world. Just a great example of how to treat people.
Delicious. Good attention. Love this place!
Fresh and delicious. Wish the red sauce was spicier

Great Mediterranean food. Service is quick, you move through the line while they build your meal based on which options you want for protein, sides, sauces, etc. After eating, I always feel full but not stuffed.
Really good, healthy and quality food. I ordered Chicken Roti. I liked it!

I had a wonderful experience here. Lovely staff blessed me with his genrousity once he knew it was my 1st time. I wasn't really expecting much, however the food was absolutely great! The Humus is world class. My plate looked awesome down the order line and tasted even better. I'm definitely visting again for more. Highly recommended
One of the best Mediterranean restaurant in Chicago, definitely can try.
Fresh food, great portions.
Service was good, food ok. Didn't have much flavors to it, I guess ok for fast food.
A very nice Mediterranean place to grab a quick bite. Taste good and quick service.
Amazing food.
Good mix of options
Fast even during the lunch rush, very friendly and attentive staff, plenty of space to sit, and of course  fresh and delicious food!
Best lunch around!!

Pretty much the same as the other Rotis in the Loop, although this location seems larger than most. Line was long, but it went fast, service is good, be ready to tell them what you want , they hustle you along. Flavors seem to have a bit too much vinegar for me compared to other Middle Eastern 'inspired' places, I can't exactly place it, but something is a bit off.
Healthy and delicious! They don't charge for extras. You can get whatever you want in your wrap or pita.
Great food.
Healthy and flavorful food!! had pita with spiced lamb meatballs and I enjoyed every bite of it.
Very friendly staff and well managed.
I love roti!!!!! 😍😍😍!
I   like   the   food it is  best  in  town
Good and healthy, but not cheap

This is a decent place. The food is good if a little expensive - $31 for 3 and we did not get extras or drinks. I haven't been to one of these in 10 years. They feel a lot like an Indian based Chipotle - very similar layout, structure and delivery. I have to be careful as once a long time agoi got something that had too much garlic and I was tasting it for 2 days (I think it was the garlic). I would probably go back again although not frequently as it feels pricey.
I like the food here very much.. queue is not bad in lunch hour.
Might go 3.5 stars. It's ok for mass Mediterranean. Don't care for their falafel.  Chicken rice bowl is decent.
Delicious healthy food,  pleasant staff, reasonable prices
Super and healthy food
Fast, fresh food. Nice change of pace
Good food, quick service, however a bit expensive for lunch.
Spicy lamb meatballs is a good addition to the menu. Real tasty dish. I wish meat portions were a bit big. ;)

This is one of my go-to places for work lunch. I usually get the chicken kabob salad, with veg and the new green shug sauce, which is addicting. The place is usually packed, though, so I definitely recommend pre-ordering, then you can just sail in, grab your food, and wave to the 50 grumpy people in line! 😉

They assemble your food according to the options chosen. Kind of Mediterraneanish faster food, great for lunch or takeout. Really, who is kidding you, it is a far cry from authentic, but, perhaps good enough for North American tastes. Surely great for fast moving, instant culture in the loop setting. They do play up healthy food like organic ingredients, antibiotic free chicken, whole  wheat bread, sustainably raised (farmed) salmon etc. Also they seem to be very good at catering office parties and other events. Good and fast, not great. Surely worth a try.
Great, fresh food, and despite the lines at lunch, they are FAST.
I love the food here. This place is nice and clean and the staff were good. It has a good parking lot.
Really tasty, light food! And great employees.

The menu options are similar to other Mediterranean/Middle Eastern lunch spots (wrap/sandwich or bowl or salad with your choice of meat/falafel and vegetables). They do have a larger selection of vegetables than other places. However, I prefer Naf Naf Grill over Roti for their flavors, pita, and larger portion size.
Fast Mediterranean food - good for what it is, but nothing special
Roti is a really good lunch spot in The Loop. They serve the food quickly, and it is always delicious (I love the Spicy Lamb Meatballs!)
Great place to eat fresh cheap healthy food
Chicken roti was awesome

Always a popular selection with my guests when I pick Roti for several business events I've hosted.  Going with selections of various wraps makes it easy to order and a snap for everyone to grab halves of different items to try.  Delivery charge is a bit pricey but the wraps come with a choice of various sides so you get a fair amount of food.  As usual my primarily meat-eating attendees skip over much of the falafel wraps which are equally great, so keep that in mind when ordering, or just convince them to try some :)

Fair is fair, we ordered from them for an office party and so they asked us to come to their customer appreciation event.  The food I like there the most is the spanikopita and the chicken skewers. The baklava is pretty good, but im not a fan of baklava in general. I really like their raspberry pie too. but the rolls left me dry :*(  I went to their outlet on Jackson, good to go there for a work lunch. Simple and easy clean and quick.
Wonderful gluten-free options
Decent food, liked the freshness
Roti is pretty good. And they give a good portion of food. Although sometimes I find seeds and stems in the food
I usually like Roti, but this location isn't very fulfilling or flavorful. Or perhaps it was because I ordered after work, when the entrees are just leftovers from lunch.
Small meat portions
So good!
My favorite Mediterranean lunch place in the loop... service is quick, the food is fresh. Don't hesitate to try the iced tea selection. Even when it's crowded you can usually get a seat.
Solid lunch option. This location seems less busy than some of the others.
This is a great quick serve Mediterranean restaurant. Food is always good for the price and speed with plenty of options. Staff is friendly.
Yummy Mediterranean food
Not so Mediterranean by the way
Good Mediterranean fast food...
I love this location! The food is great and the service is great, too ✨❤️
Good lunch option if you like Mediterranean food with a modern touch.
Food use to be good few years ago. Now everything taste like stale and blant. Do not even try their falafel, dry and you can choke on them.

Fast Mediterranean custom food place. Whatever you have, it gets you extremely full! Their pricing is moderate, definitely not cheap food. Would be better if all the sides/toppings & sauces were labeled next to the tray/warmer so it's easy for a first time person to order. If you are a first timer, take a look at the "menu" in my review or online before you come.
Simply amazing! I eat here everyday! Literally!
Great food. The salmon is amazing. I just don't like their spoons
They're falafels are probably my favorite in the city🤔
Standard noting amazing.
Awesome place for lunch
Like the food..especially the chicken kabab
Roti is my favorite fast food place in the Loop.  Everything I've had here is delicious and the service is very quick.
Busy during lunch hour and not much place to sit. Like the food.
Long Lines during lunch but quality food.

beautiful food for a great price.  customer service was fast and on point with a good variety of Greek dishes.  excellent food quality given in good portions that adds up to a lunch that keeps you filled until you clock out from work.  best place for lunch under 10$
Good food, line moves quick!
It's like a chipotle for Mediterranean food. Good food, it's fast and clean.
Cheap, quick and tasty food.
Lovely food and menu... top-notch customer service..
Mediterranean food. Do I really have to say more? Our office sometimes orders catering from them and I love the variety of dishes. The hummus is one of my favorite out of all the downtown options.
Really like this place, fast, great tasting, good for a quick lunch. We sometimes order for the whole office, it's a favorite!
Very Nice Restaurant with amazing fast service. We had Falafel Sandwich and Hummus with Pita Bread. We loved the food. Food is a little pricy for mediterranean Grill.
Love this place - food is bomb and the staff is awesome. Can't go wrong!

Love this food. Fresh and tasty food that's much more interesting than normal places. Staff here is always helpful and friendly. Just wish they would be better about having all the meat options ready.
One of my favorite places to grab lunch. The spicy sauce tastes fantastic on the chicken roti.
Good food
Small outdoor seating available but can get a little noisy outside when the train passes by
Average food . Lacks true Mediterranean flavors
Great customer service. Spoken to Someone name Carolyn and she help me out with everything being my first time eating at Roti. definitely will be returning soon!

For $8 a plate, a great place. Staff is wonderful. Food was delicious. There is one row of window seating wth a tall table that worked great for me sitting in my wheelchair. The rest of the seating is the regular, low height tables.
If you're craving a Mediterranean rendition on Chipotle - look no further.

This spot hit my hunger spot every time. It's an order as you go place, where you order the start, the meat, and the toppings as you go down the line. I love getting a roti pita sandwich but it always ended overflowing with toppings, so I have to eat it like a salad at first. If you like spicy, get the S'hug sauce! It's one of the best hot sauce ever.
I love mediterranean food. Roti is pretty awesome. I came in with a half off coupon and got a very filling and nutritious lunch for less than $5. Will be back!

I usually go to the Roti at 33 N. Dearborn before going to Broadway in Chicago, but this location is right near the Cadillac Palace Theatre and I met friends here before a show.  That said, they were not at all prepared for dinner service at 6pm on Tuesday and did not have pitas ready nor chicken, which they had to prepare as we waited 5-10 minutes for the kabob meat on the grill.  They only made enough to serve 2 people and by the time that was ready, there were another 8-10 customers in line - many wanting chicken.  The plus was that it was made to order, and so were the pitas but it took forever.  I ordered mine as a wrap which was very sloppily put together and very messy to eat.  In general, I will go back to the Dearborn location for dinner service and leave this one to deal with the lunch rush.
Really good food plenty to eat for a great price.

Not bad for a quick mediterranean meal. They have an impeccable gluten free cross contamination prevention policy (one person changes their gloves and handles your plate down the entire assembly line) and the fact that they offer gluten free pita is excellent.  The food is tasty, but I've had better hummus and shwarma. I love the roasted veggies, though!

I've been to this location about 4 times and the staff is absolutely wonderful.  However, the last two times I have gone, I have ordered steak and they had to prepare it while I was there (I guess they ran out of the prepared steak).  Anyway, both times, I ordered the steak sandwich and when I got back to work, I realized the the steak was nicely browned on the outside and COMPLETELY RAW on the inside. Ugh.  I hope I don't get food poisoning and I hope that the friendly workers learn to cook the steak properly.  I think I will get vegetarian if they don't have any prepared meats next time I go.
Yum and lots of great bread on the side! I love feta and they have great meats too! Love their sides and that they bring some Mediterranean to the city!
You get large portion sizes and pretty good food for the price. When we went near closing time, they gave us containers of free hummus and pita chips, which was awesome.

Found Roti by accident for lunch one day. Thought food was wonderful and extremely inexpensive especially for downtown. Spoke with a friend about Roti. She said top Chipotle execs resigned to invest in Roti so expect to see more locations popping up soon. Can't wait!!
The staff at this location is so friendly.  I like that you can view the menu prior to getting to the front of the line.  Good pick for a healthy lunch on the go.

My husband and I came to this location for lunch because of the ease of finding a parking spot, but after receiving our food, we quickly found out that convenience and quantity can't replace quality. we got bigger portioned scoops of rice and toppings but the broccoli and carrots (grilled vegetables) were ice cold. I was also charged for an additional sauce on the side. :-( I guess we will continue to visit the Dearborn location where the food is hot, the sauce is free and having my husband to circle the block is well worth it!
